This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating photo-realistic images of a face. It also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and conditional generative adversarial networks (cGANs), which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

It could also belong to the signal processing (cs.SD) sub-category as it involves processing audio input to generate mouth landmarks. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with generating images and audio in sync. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as the paper involves the use of RNNs and cGANs, which are machine learning techniques. 

Finally, natural language processing (cs.CL) could be a potential sub-category as the paper deals with generating lip sync for audio input, which is related to speech processing.
